verbose_text: Rectal cancer recurrence was associated with a body mass index greater than 25 kg/m 2 (P = 0.0001), a larger tumor size (6.00 +/- 0.34; P < 0.001), advanced T stage (P < 0.005), higher serum CEA levels (P < 0.002), poor differentiation or mucinous histology (P < 0.007), perineural invasion (P < 0.001), vascular invasion (P = 0.028), and infiltration of lymphatic vessels (P < 0.001).
